Tweet: Today @SoCo_TPW crews are on site to remove burned trees within the road right-of-way in preparation for residents to be able to return to evacuated areas. For updates on all disaster-related information, please visit https://socoemergency.org/ . #SonomaCountyStrong #KincadeFirepic.twitter.com/WDkj7bUvwP
Route 60X begins operation Wed., 10/30, between #Cloverdale and #RohnertPark to provide access to grocery stores and pharmacies for residents impacted by the power shutoff and fire disaster.

Rte. 60 express (60X) begins operation Wed., 10/31, thru Fri., 11/1, btw. #Cloverdale and #RohnertPark. Southbound passengers transfer from Rte. 68 at Cloverdale Market stop. Northbound passengers transfer to Rte. 68 at City Hall stop. More: https://sctransit.com/ #SonomaCountypic.twitter.com/Rif8HiibxG
NOTICE: the community warming/charging station in #Cloverdale will remain in place until 8 p.m. and reopen tomorrow, 10/30, from 6 a.m. - 6 p.m.

. @Fly_STS Aircraft Rescue & Firefighting (ARFF) unit provides mutal aid out of #Cloverdale airport for @CAL_FIRE air attack on #KincadeFire. @SoCo_TPW stands ready and continues to assist in response, hazard mitigation, & evacuation efforts. Updates: https://socoemergency.org/ pic.twitter.com/MiHKxpjhgb

@SoCo_TPW officials installed 40 ft. bus at #Cloverdale City Hall to serve as community warming/charging station until 4 p.m. today. Driver on site can provide info in English and Spanish. Local free shuttle Route 68 is also in service. Transit alerts: https://sctransit.com/ .pic.twitter.com/Ah3h5u9hEk

REMINDER: All #SonomaCounty Transit services are cancelled for Sunday, October 27 and Monday, October 28 as resources are directed towards providing emergency transportation related to the #KincadeFire. More: https://sctransit.com/

#SonomaCounty TPW Update: FIRE ROAD CLOSURES: Expect all roads east of Hwy 128 from Cloverdale to Healdsburg to be closed due to the Kincade fire. Visit http://roadconditions.sonoma-county.org/ for an up-to-the-minute listing of Road Closures & Delays. Drive safe!

#SonomaCounty TPW Update: Laughlin Road in Santa Rosa is closed at the bridge due to a vehicle accident. Visit http://roadconditions.sonoma-county.org/ for an up-to-the-minute listing of Road Closures & Delays. Drive safe!

ADVISORY: Laughlin Rd. will be closed this morning to remove a stuck semi-trailer truck from the Laughlin Rd. bridge. Trucks longer than 38 ft. have been prohibited from traveling the road since 2014. #Vultures #SonomaCounty Background: https://bit.ly/2yYXmC9 pic.twitter.com/nnfi91ECVz

#SonomaCounty TPW Update: Warm Springs Road in Kenwood will have reduced lanes in the area of address 1154 due to tree work. 9am to 1pm today, 10/23/19. Visit http://roadconditions.sonoma-county.org/ for an up-to-the-minute listing of Road Closures & Delays. Drive safe!
